title: Arlene Francis & Skitch Henderson
description: "The MATCH GAME" is a Game of Compared Judgments of Answers to the Fill-in-the-Blank & Survey Questions are asked by the host of 'The MATCH GAME' Gene Rayburn to 2 Teams (6 Members including 2 Star Team Captains) write down the answer to a question and once both 2 Teams finished writing their own answers and the host asked one of them show the 1st Answer that wrote and the 2nd Answer that wrote also that makes a "MATCH" and scores 10 points and the 3rd Answer that wrote by The Star Team Captain as well becomes a "MATCH" and scores 20 points. The 1st Team scores 100 points or Greater than that wins $100 or Expensive than that to play "The AUDIENCE MATCH" to win $450 and consisted of 3 Secret Survey Questions that takes place on certain number of weekdays before going on the air. Each Member of the Winning Team including the Star Team Captain must answer the question will be matched after they're spoken for the following breakdown. For 1 Member Matched the Top Answer Secretly wins $50, 2 Members Matched the Top Answer Secretly wins $100 & All 3 Members of the Team including the Star Team Captain Matched the Top Answer Secretly wins $150. After 3 Questions asked The Team collected $450 or Cheaper than that will be added to $100 for the total $550 or Expensive than that.
